                <span class="content-container-2">
                    <h3 class="expansion">Emily Gonzales (she/her)</h3>
                    <p class="minor-expansion">Co-Mentor to Kit & Cohort, Guest Speaker: Critical Race Theory and Global Dynamics- Advanced Semester</p>
                </span>
                <span class="content-container-2">
                    <h4 class="minor-expansion">Role: Executive Director / Director of Education</h4>
                </span>
                <img src="/img/emily.png" alt="Emily smiles at the camera, with Black hair and red lipstick" class="photo-image">
                <span class="content-container-3 mint">
                    <p>Emily serves as Executive Director of the <a href="https://swellcollective.org/">Swell Collective</a>, a BIPOC & Queer-led organization whose mission is to inspire, equip and amplify change agents representing marginalized communities. She is a master trainer and facilitator of radical collaboration and dialogue with an approach that centers equity and resilience. Her academic research focuses on social capital generation in socio-technical systems, and human/social capital as untapped sources of wealth and power for the systemically marginalized. She is a native Californian, tech geek and certified yoga instructor, mother of a 11 year old superhero, and life partners with an active duty Marine, residing in Oceanside, CA.</p>
                </span>
            </span>
